  "texts": [
    "For accuracy evaluation, we measured the area under the receiver operating characteristic curve (AUROC) on all patch images using their predicted confidence scores and their true labels for PCa presence.",
    "These test conditions replicate the challenge of cancer detection on images originating from slides with faded staining to assess the limitations of our approach.",
    "We measured the association between the predicted and true tumor volumes in 46 prostatectomy specimens with complete delineation of cancer lesions (368 slides).",
    "We utilized the well-established grid method, which was described in detail in our previous study 4.",
    "In brief, we defined a two-dimensional space for each slide where a single patch image corresponded to a pixel (a pixel corresponded to a 512 × 512 µm dimension of a slide image at the 10 × objective magnification level)."
  ],
